summary: There’s a version of Killing Eve that moves much slower than the version that exists. Is much more violent than the version that...
text:
There’s a version of Killing Eve that moves much slower than the version that exists. Is much more violent than the version that exists. Is much grimmer than the version that exists. Thankfully, the version that exists is better than any of those other options.

In many ways, the show is a much more palatable, female-centric version of Bryan Fuller’s Hannibal. It too is a stylized off-kilter cop vs mentally distorted but highly organized killer story, but unlike Fuller’s cult classic, Killing Eve goes out of its way to bring just a hint of levity to its depths.

In no way should one expect a bright series from Killing Eve. It’s as dark and demented as anything else out there, but it also has the good sense to not live in the dark for any one particularly long stretch of time.
